Set line console and vty password in switch command
Hostname floor1-sw    #this is the name of switch 
Line console 0
Password cisco      #paassword is cisco
Login 
Exit
Line vty 0 15
Password cicso      # paassword is cisco
Login 
Exit
No ip domain-lookup   #wrong command will not impact cli that why we sued it
Enable password cisco   #protech admin mode if we not used it anyone can be the admin
Service password encryption   #hide the password
Do wr
_______________________________________________________________________________________
Add security to layer 2 switch
Switch port-security
 Switch port-security maximum 2
Switch port-security mac address sticky
Switch port-security violation shutdown
Do wr
Connect ssh in router command for remote login-
hostname f3-router                                  #give router a name 
ip domain-name gtech                              # add domain name where gtech is name 
username gtech passward getech           #add username and password
crypto key generate rsa                              # it generate crypto key where you have to write 1024 and it show 
                                                                            shh is enable            
line vty 0 15
login local
transport input ssh 
do wr              
#now if you want to connet router from any pc you used command 
Ssh -l gtech 10.10.10.1                             #gtech si username name and 10.10.10.1 is router ip        
Password:
F2-rpoouter>                                             #this will show means connect
Exit
_______________________________________________________________________________________                                                                                                                                         
Ospf setup in router-
Router ospf 10 
Network 10.10.10.0 255.0.0.0  area 0   #add all network same like this way which is connected to router
Network 10.10.10.1 255.0.0.0  area 0   
_______________________________________________________________________________________


Rip v2 routing protocol-
Router rip
Version 2
Network 10.10.10.0   #all connected network in router
